  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2018-01-11",
    "date": "2018-12-27T17:31:15Z",
    "text": "Veterans Deserve Better Act\n\nThis bill amends the Veterans Access, Choice, and Accountability Act of 2014 to require: (1) the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) to pay for hospital care or medical services furnished by a non-VA health care entity or provider under the Veterans Choice Program within 45 days of receipt of a paper claim or within 30 days of receipt of an electronic claim, and (2) the entity or provider to file a claim with the VA within 180 days of providing the service.\n\nThe VA shall bar providers or entities that file fraudulent health claims from program participation.\n\nThe VA shall: (1) ensure that contracts with third party administrators require that veterans' health care appointments be scheduled within five days, and (2) track all appointments and follow up on delayed appointments."
  },
